# Project Rules and Persistent Agent Memories

## ⚠️ Critical Deployment Checklist
When modifying any environment variables (`PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SCRIPT_URL`, `DASHBOARD_API_TOKEN`, etc.) in `.env` files:
1. **GitHub Secrets:** You must remind the user to update the corresponding secrets in the GitHub Repository Settings (**Settings -> Secrets and variables -> Actions -> Repository secrets**). The frontend is built as a static site via GitHub Actions, which embeds `PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SCRIPT_URL` at compile-time. If the secret is not updated, the production site will use the old/broken URL.
2. **VPS Deployment:** Remind the user to sync the `.env` file to the VPS (directory `/opt/svatba-dashboard/` or equivalent) so the Python script `update_dashboard.py` can load it.
3. **Local Dev Server:** Remind the user to restart the Astro dev server (`npm run dev`) since it only loads `.env` variables on startup.

## 🛠️ Google Apps Script Configuration
* **Spustit jako / Execute as:** Must be set to "Já / Me" (e.g. `filipvalasek@gmail.com`).
* **Kdo má přístup / Who has access:** Must be set to "Kdokoli / Anyone".
* **Deployment Updates:** Any script changes must be deployed as a "New version" (Nové nasazení or Spravovat nasazení -> Upravit -> Nová verze -> Nasadit) to take effect.
* **Typo warning:** The URL ID contains case-sensitive characters. For example, `AKfycbxu4pTV0kljCj2IxflZP...` has a capital `I` (Igloo), not a lowercase `l` (lemon) on index 21.

## 🤖 Form Submission Debugging
* If form submissions silently fail (i.e. UI shows success but spreadsheet is not populated):
  1. Open Browser DevTools (F12) -> Console. Check for `"Spam submission blocked."` or `"Spam detected."`. This indicates the honeypot field (`website_hp`) was autofilled by the browser.
  2. Open Browser DevTools (F12) -> Network. Check if the POST request goes to the correct script URL.

## 📡 Morse Code Guidelines
* **Legibility:** Morse code dash symbols must always be written using the em-dash (`—`, U+2014) instead of standard hyphens (`-`) or mathematical minus signs (`−`). This keeps them highly distinguishable from dots (`·`).
* **Visual Separation:** Morse content elements must always include sufficient `letter-spacing` (e.g. via Tailwind tracking utility or CSS style) to prevent consecutive dashes (like `——` or `———`) from blending into a single continuous line.
* **Audio & Translator Sync:** When adding new Morse decoding/encoding or sound functionality, ensure the script Translator and Audio classes handle the em-dash (`—`) character correctly.
